  "texts": [
    "Thus, compared with the question generation solution by Dijkstra et al. (2022), Sharma et al. (2022) obtained a more competitive METEOR value.",
    "Ultimately, Nasution (2023) used GPT-3.5 for question generation.",
    "To assess the generated questions' reliability or internal consistency, the Cronbach's alpha coefficient (Taber, 2018) was computed, resulting in 0.65.",
    "Answers from a survey performed to almost 300 students show that 79% of the generated questions were relevant, 72% were moderately clear, and 71% were of enough depth.",
    "In contrast, Phillips et al. (2022) used GPT-3 to create summaries of students' chats in collaborative learning."
